  label: "Venture Capital Investment Cycles",
  summary: "Venture capital investment cycles refer to the recurring patterns of investment, growth, and sometimes contraction within the venture capital industry, driven by economic conditions, technological trends, and investor sentiment. In AI policy, understanding these cycles is important for analyzing the pace and direction of AI development, identifying potential bubbles or funding gaps, and considering how government policies might influence private investment in AI research and commercialization.",
