  summary: "Whistleblower protection frameworks are the established legal, regulatory, and organizational structures designed to protect individuals who report illegal, unethical, or harmful activities within an organization. In AI policy, these frameworks are vital for creating a culture of transparency and accountability, enabling employees and researchers to safely report concerns about AI bias, misuse, or safety risks without fear of retaliation, thereby contributing to the responsible development and deployment of AI.",
