  summary: "Worker solidarity movements are organized efforts by groups of workers to collectively advance their shared interests, often through unions, protests, or advocacy for better working conditions, wages, and rights. In AI policy, these movements are increasingly relevant as AI automation impacts employment, labor practices, and the nature of work, raising questions about fair transitions for displaced workers, the ethical use of AI in workplace surveillance, and the need for collective bargaining in an AI-driven economy.",
